  "description": "Figure-Eight topology at braidDepth 0.72 — well above WEAVE-I — in the bass register. The alternating polarity coupling creates internal motion that no standard bass synthesis approach can produce: the four strands argue in four directions simultaneously, their over/under crossings creating a woven low-end texture. The 700 Hz filter removes the high-frequency intermodulation products, leaving only the topology's effect on the fundamental and its immediate harmonics. macroKnot=0.28 bleeds Torus surface symmetry into the Figure-Eight polarity, softening the most extreme reversals. A bass that breathes from the inside.",
